= Abstract

Nanyang OJ is an online programming contest platform intended for school use. This project develops the frontend of Nanyang OJ. The motivation of the project is to create a contest system that can be owned and
managed by the school, so that contest configuration, participant experience, and future extensions can be controlled by school instead of external platforms.

My contribution focuses on the participant-facing frontend. I designed the initial user interface and user experience based on the requirements using Figma and implemented the main React pages for contest participation, including login and signup,
contest list and contest detail pages, problem pages, submission views, FAQ, and user
profile. The frontend is built with TypeScript, React, and Material UI. It communicates with
the backend through API service layer which handles authentication, request
structure, and response validation.

The later stage of the project involved continuous revision, maintenance, and improvement of the
frontend system and its integration with the backend. Through iterative refinement of features,
data handling, and overall system behavior, the platform became more stable, consistent, and complete.

Overall, the project demonstrates the design and implementation of a maintainable contest frontend
that supports a consistent participant workflow and provides a practical foundation for a
school-owned online judge and contest platform.
